 Reduction 

In section , we have argued that there
exists a range of energies where the theory is
effectively 5 dimensional, as illustrated in
Fig. 2.


In this appendix we show the dimensional reduction
procedure from  dimensions down to 5 dimensions,
which allows contact with the language of
.

The reduction from the higher dimensional theory
() to 5 dimensions is performed by the
compactification on the internal manifold . This amounts
to keeping only the -zero modes of the fields defined in
 dimensions.

In this section we denote
collectively the four dimensional Minkowski coordinates
 and the orbifold 
by . 

